On Sun, 18 May 2003, Terry K. wrote:

> My 74 flex plate has three hex headed bolts.
> 
> All of them do---
> 
> Any FLAPS shoud be able to accomodate you if you need some new ones--
> Just make sure they are grade eight bolts. 

there are 5 socket bolts holding the drive plate to the crankshaft, there
are 3 hex bolts between the flexplate and the torque converter...these 3
bolts are NOT INTERCHANGABLE they have special heads...others can damage
the torqueconverter or bell housing

